    "result": "**`internal/watch`** watches the project's root directory for filesystem changes and drives incremental re-indexing. When a burst of save events arrives, it waits for a quiet window (debounce), then triggers a full indexer pass. Overlapping events are coalesced — if a run is already in progress, pending changes queue up for the next cycle. An optional `OnIdle` callback fires after a longer period of quiet (used to drain background summaries).\n\n**Debounce default: `500ms`** (`Options.Debounce`). The `OnIdle` quiet window defaults to `5s` when `OnIdle` is set.",
